The evolution of human communication has been about removing whatever bottl=
eneck is in this value chain. Before humans could write, information could =
only be conveyed orally; that meant that the creation, vocalization, delive=
ry, and consumption of an idea were all one-and-the-same. Writing, though, =
unbundled consumption, increasing the number of people who could consume an=
 idea.

